    "116834511": {
      "title": "The finite difference time domain method for the study of two-dimensional acoustic and elastic gap materials",
      "abstract": "The finite difference time domain (FDTD) method has been proved recently an excellent tool for the study of classical wave propagation in periodic and random composite systems. Here we present in detail the method as it is applied in the case of acoustic and elastic wave propagation in two-dimensional composites. Also, we present some representative results of the method and we discuss its advantages."
